There have been a number of reports of bomb threats in recent weeks, throughout Skopje and outside the capital, at airports, hotels, shopping centres, sporting centres, and schools.  Local authorities have investigated, and declared all threats so far to be false alarms. Follow the directions of the local authorities and police.
Terrorists are likely to try to carry out attacks in North Macedonia. Attacks could be indiscriminate, including in places visited by foreigners. Terrorists may target religious sites, including churches.
